1
00:00:00,031 --> 00:00:27,844
Namo tassa bhagavato harahato samma sambuddhassa Namo tassa bhagavato harahato samma sambuddhassa Namo tassa bhagavato harahato samma sambuddhassa

2
00:00:28,448 --> 00:00:35,499
homage to the Buddha, the blessed, noble and fully self-enlightened.

3
00:00:35,518 --> 00:00:50,661
So continuing with these perfections, and remember that's an odd sort of translation, it's those virtues, actions that we need to arrive at the other shore, that's what parami means, the other shore.

4
00:00:50,843 --> 00:00:56,210
It's just the Buddha's way of talking about Nibbana, it's that other place, transcendent place.

5
00:00:56,191 --> 00:01:05,968
And what he says is, when he's asked the question, or when he asks the question, what is karmically wholesome morality?

6
00:01:06,911 --> 00:01:12,781
It is wholesome bodily actions, wholesome verbal actions and purity of livelihood.

7
00:01:12,762 --> 00:01:33,555
So, when we talk about sila, morality, it really is confined to outward actions, to the way we affect the world through our actions, our speech, and through our livelihood.

8
00:01:35,037 --> 00:01:41,445
It starts with the negative propositions.

9
00:01:42,147 --> 00:01:43,468
So there are various levels.

10
00:01:43,549 --> 00:01:54,004
The first one is this five, the Panchasila, the five C. Carpita, which means root training rules.

11
00:01:54,024 --> 00:01:55,546
And that's what we chant in the evening.

12
00:01:56,206 --> 00:02:00,352
So they're pretty basic to any society.

13
00:02:00,332 --> 00:02:07,376
kill each other, kill beings in that sense, but to kill other human beings.

14
00:02:07,397 --> 00:02:10,527
And we're not going to steal, take what is not freely given.

15
00:02:10,794 --> 00:02:13,538
Not misuse our sexual powers.

16
00:02:14,479 --> 00:02:16,262
Not to use wrong speech.

17
00:02:16,842 --> 00:02:22,109
That's divided into both telling figs and lying.

18
00:02:23,270 --> 00:02:25,492
Slanderous speech, doing people down.

19
00:02:28,637 --> 00:02:33,522
Slanderous speech, gossip, just wasting time.

20
00:02:34,644 --> 00:02:36,606
Oh, there's one other.

21
00:02:36,806 --> 00:02:37,527
It'll come to me.

22
00:02:38,234 --> 00:02:42,680
So, and then finally, of course, intoxicants.

23
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:45,524
Nothing that's going to affect our consciousness.

24
00:02:46,966 --> 00:02:50,570
So those are your five sort of basic not-to-dos.

25
00:02:51,532 --> 00:02:59,424
And obviously, once we stop behaving like that, then it becomes more and more refined.

26
00:02:59,965 --> 00:03:04,651
So, whereas it's not killing human beings, we don't want to harm any living beings.

27
00:03:05,633 --> 00:03:07,194
So there's a refinement of that.

28
00:03:07,444 --> 00:03:09,106
And then of course it transforms.

29
00:03:09,567 --> 00:03:14,393
So from not wanting to harm any living beings, we want to protect them.

30
00:03:15,133 --> 00:03:22,481
So that's the sort of process, starting with that sort of very negative formulation, and we end up with a very positive one.

31
00:03:23,043 --> 00:03:25,746
So it's the same with taking what is not freely given.

32
00:03:27,687 --> 00:03:31,612
So from sort of gross thieving from the banks and stuff like that.

33
00:03:32,014 --> 00:03:38,837
To being careful even with simple things like not taking pens from work, stuff like that.

34
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:41,366
One gets very sensitive about that.

35
00:03:41,616 --> 00:03:47,566
But of course what one moves towards is generosity, giving away.

36
00:03:48,007 --> 00:04:03,512
Sexual energy and that is refined in the sense that it moves from only using that energy within a skillful relationship, a loving relationship.

37
00:04:03,532 --> 00:04:07,437
And of course if you're not in relationship then it moves you towards celibacy.

38
00:04:08,008 --> 00:04:16,641
And celibacy is not just simply, it's not a denial of sexual energy, it's a transformation of it, it's a sublimation of it.

39
00:04:17,201 --> 00:04:23,630
Sublimation is not a word we come across these days, because I think we get confused about suppressing.

40
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:29,699
But suppressing something is a negative thing.

41
00:04:29,779 --> 00:04:35,146
It's about pushing something away out of negativity or fear.

42
00:04:35,583 --> 00:04:46,689
but sublimating is seeing that actually what there is is just energy and through our conditioning we've channeled it in certain areas

43
00:04:47,108 --> 00:05:09,031
And if we've channeled it into our sexual appetite, then it's a case of, as it were, letting that energy move over towards something more skillful, if we can't use our energy as a sexual energy.

44
00:05:09,692 --> 00:05:11,194
It's not stuck there.

45
00:05:11,894 --> 00:05:16,980
So that's a sort of refinement of that energy.

46
00:05:19,254 --> 00:05:37,242
When it comes to speech, you know, the speech moves from coarse speech, that was the one I missed out, coarse speech, we move towards truthfulness, truthfulness, kindly speech, and speech at an appropriate time.

47
00:05:37,882 --> 00:05:48,738
So often we're being truthful, we're being kind, but we're not quite choosing the right situation to say what we want to say, and it causes upset, as if we had just waited and

48
00:05:49,107 --> 00:05:57,235
for the opportunity, then we would have been able to have said something to help a situation, you see.

49
00:05:58,036 --> 00:06:01,420
So you've got these refinements.

50
00:06:01,721 --> 00:06:03,444
And the last one is intoxication.

51
00:06:03,543 --> 00:06:07,267
So basically, you know, in the spiritual life, you want to keep your consciousness clear.

52
00:06:07,348 --> 00:06:08,949
You want to keep it awake.

53
00:06:09,790 --> 00:06:14,776
So putting anything there is not, putting anything into consciousness is going to distort it.

54
00:06:15,377 --> 00:06:16,819
It's exactly what you don't want to do.

55
00:06:17,237 --> 00:06:21,204
and the refinement of it is this moment-to-moment awareness.

56
00:06:21,485 --> 00:06:24,250
That's what we're moving towards.

57
00:06:24,269 --> 00:06:27,716
So those, you might say, are your basic platform of practice.

58
00:06:28,517 --> 00:06:36,572
And then the Buddha sort of gives an opportunity to lay people to, as we say, turn the screw a bit on the full moon days.

59
00:06:36,632 --> 00:06:42,182
That's when, in Theravada Buddha's country, the person might practice the eight

60
00:06:42,567 --> 00:06:47,531
Sīla, the eight, Sīkāpita, the eight rules of training.

61
00:06:47,916 --> 00:07:09,463
So on a full moon day or a new moon day, you might find that people go to the local monastery and there they take slightly monastic vows in the sense that they don't eat after lunch, they don't worry about entertainment, they let go of radio, TV, iPods, all that sort of stuff.

62
00:07:09,543 --> 00:07:14,649
They don't worry about self-beautification, cosmetics, jewelry, all that sort of stuff.

63
00:07:14,629 --> 00:07:39,692
and and they don't if they're staying overnight they're just happy with just a straightforward bed luxurious abandoning luxurious beds so those those training rules are as it were finding out where your attachments are that's what these that's what they're about and

64
00:07:41,038 --> 00:07:46,526
By doing that, of course, you've got something to work with because it's attachments that we have to undermine.

65
00:07:46,586 --> 00:07:52,795
Then there's the entrance into the order, what we call the samanera.

66
00:07:52,896 --> 00:07:55,800
So that moves into a ten precepts.

67
00:07:55,821 --> 00:08:02,310
And it's the same as the eight, except the bit about entertainment and beautification are made into two.

68
00:08:02,870 --> 00:08:06,776
But added to that is this business of not touching money, not using money.

69
00:08:07,127 --> 00:08:14,516
So you're retreating from the world, from the world of enticement, you see, once you've got no money, that's it.

70
00:08:15,576 --> 00:08:22,504
And then finally when you join the order, there's a 227, it leaps, it's sort of a quantum leap into 227.

71
00:08:24,788 --> 00:08:31,514
And again the whole idea of the rules is that part of it is based on that moral, the moral rule,

72
00:08:31,951 --> 00:08:54,921
of not to harm living beings and so on but the other side of it are just institutional rules which are meant to help the monastic remain more and more mindful so clothes for instance you know like it never occurs to me to get up in the morning and think I shall wear blue today it's just this is it I've just got these robes and that's the end of it

73
00:08:55,205 --> 00:09:03,317
And it stops any worry or concern about how you look or how you should look, because you all look the same.

74
00:09:03,517 --> 00:09:12,269
The whole idea is to draw a line as to what it is you want to get involved with when it comes to the world.

75
00:09:14,153 --> 00:09:19,760
Food, you see, we only eat what we are given, so we don't choose what to eat.

76
00:09:20,855 --> 00:09:29,543
So those are sort of refinements in terms of letting go of wants, the ordinary wants of life, you see.

77
00:09:29,563 --> 00:09:45,039
And, you know, a lot of this sort of stuff the layperson can also practice, you know, just reducing the amount of, I mean, looking at your wardrobe and just asking, you know, do I need all this stuff, you know, how many pairs of shoes do you need, you see.

78
00:09:47,482 --> 00:09:59,804
So that's the sort of how the morality in Buddha's understanding works because morality is the measure of wisdom or lack of it.

79
00:10:00,460 --> 00:10:02,883
So wisdom isn't something abstract.

80
00:10:03,024 --> 00:10:06,248
Wisdom is a way of relating to the world.

81
00:10:06,327 --> 00:10:10,374
It's not a knowledge, it's a relationship, a wise relationship.

82
00:10:10,955 --> 00:10:19,366
And this mirrors itself in our attitudes and this goes outwards into the world in right speech, right action and then right livelihood.

83
00:10:20,368 --> 00:10:23,633
So this right livelihood, for instance,

84
00:10:24,169 --> 00:10:32,980
The worst of course is you don't want to get involved in the traffic of arms and human beings, flesh, intoxicants and arms.

85
00:10:34,740 --> 00:10:47,655
So once you're not involved in that, really any other form of livelihood can be taken as being something wholesome and to be used as a spiritual practice.

86
00:10:47,676 --> 00:10:51,779
That's what you do with your energy into society.

87
00:10:51,759 --> 00:11:14,072
and it's finding ways of making our livelihood and our ordinary daily lives work for us towards the spiritual end so we have to have the principles right so basically we're developing the good heart anything that we do with a good heart

88
00:11:14,490 --> 00:11:24,224
from putting our attention and care into things becomes a spiritual path, just naturally, not to worry about it.

89
00:11:24,244 --> 00:11:28,850
So that's what sila means in the Buddha's practice, in the Buddha's understanding.

90
00:11:28,910 --> 00:11:35,740
Morality, we translate it as morality or ethics, behavior, moral, moral, immoral behavior.

91
00:11:36,125 --> 00:11:45,318
And he just laid out a very simple platform that we can use to investigate our actions.

92
00:11:46,159 --> 00:11:55,754
And it's good practice, sort of, sometime in the day, sometime in the evening, just to review the day and just see whether we've been skillful or unskillful.

93
00:11:55,774 --> 00:11:56,595
So that's the words.

94
00:11:57,736 --> 00:11:59,919
That's how we translate this, kusala-akusala.

95
00:12:01,121 --> 00:12:03,785
Wholesome, unwholesome, skillful, unskillful.

96
00:12:04,647 --> 00:12:05,928
And so...

97
00:12:06,162 --> 00:12:09,715
They're not to be looked at as commandments, putting down upon us.

98
00:12:09,735 --> 00:12:16,458
They're just basic rules and regulations that come out of our human existence.

99
00:12:17,265 --> 00:12:45,736
Just being humans, this is the situation we're in, and because of our relationship to the world, we do things which are unwholesome, and they can be, in some way, fitted into these five basic laws about harm, about truthfulness, about our relationship to things, objects, taking what's not freely given.

100
00:12:46,274 --> 00:12:51,541
about our sexual energy, that can be widened out to just all appetites.

101
00:12:52,402 --> 00:13:00,994
Whether we're eating or enjoying this or enjoying that, it all comes under, in a sense, that business of greed.

102
00:13:03,417 --> 00:13:09,445
And intoxicants, just being careful not to put into the body what's going to upset our consciousness.

103
00:13:13,009 --> 00:13:13,850
So I can only hope

104
00:13:14,269 --> 00:13:16,135
My words have been of some assistance.

105
00:13:16,758 --> 00:13:29,157
May you be liberated from all suffering sooner rather than later.

